    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "Parents may understand that as they follow God&apos;s directions in the training of their children, they will receive help from on high. They receive much benefit; for as they teach, they learn. Their children will achieve victories through the knowledge that they have acquired in keeping the way of the Lord. They are enabled to overcome natural and hereditary tendencies to evil.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">4<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"RH 6-6-1899\" data-link=\"821.17999\">The Review and Herald, June 6, 1899</span>.</span></a></sup>",
